case_type.rationale: Given the nature of the dispute involving delivery delays and quality issues ('wrong gender and wrong size'), mediation provides a platform for Kal-El and A-BC Suppliers to collaboratively find a mutually acceptable solution. It allows for open communication and addresses the specific concerns regarding product specifications. Mediation is often effective in resolving contract disputes without escalating to more adversarial processes.

alternatives.reason: If mediation fails, arbitration offers a binding decision from a neutral third party, providing a more formal and conclusive resolution to the contract dispute. This is suitable if the parties require a definitive outcome.

required_documents.description: The signed contract between Kal-El and A-BC Suppliers, outlining the terms of agreement, including product specifications, delivery timelines, and quality standards.
required_documents.reason: Essential to establish the contractual obligations of both parties.

required_documents.description: Invoices related to the order, showing the items ordered, quantities, and agreed prices.
required_documents.reason: Confirms the details of the specific transaction in dispute.

required_documents.description: All email correspondence between Kal-El and A-BC Suppliers regarding the order, delivery, quality concerns, and any attempts to resolve the issues.
required_documents.reason: Provides evidence of communication, negotiations, and any admissions or acknowledgments of the issues.

required_documents.description: Photographic evidence of the delivered goods, clearly showing the wrong size or gender specifications.
required_documents.reason: Visually demonstrates the quality issues and discrepancies in product specifications.

required_documents.description: Any legal notices sent to A-BC Suppliers regarding the breach of contract.
required_documents.reason: Indicates the formal steps taken to address the dispute.
